main event: A bright white object that resembled Venus was observed in the sky over Sells, Arizona on February 28, 1966.
interesting points: The object was described as the size of a grapefruit and displayed a stellar magnitude of -4.3.,Witnesses noted that there was no sound, vapor trail, or exhaust.,The object was visible for approximately 1 and a quarter hours.,There was a debate about whether the object was a celestial body or an unidentified flying object.,Reports indicated that the brightness of the object led some to initially believe it was an unusual phenomenon.
sighted object: One bright white object resembling Venus
witness description: Various witnesses including law enforcement officers and a civilian described the object.
